THE EASY WAY:

Use CPAN, install everything needed with:

perl -MCPAN -e 'install Bundle::WebDyne'

or if you have downloaed just the WebDyne module unpack it and:

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install 

Then run:

bin/wdapacheinit

for Apache installation or

bin/wdlighttpdinit

for Lighttpd installation

the location of bin/wd... will be distribution dependent - you may have to
hunt it down after installation.

THE HARD WAY:

Download and install the WebDyne::Doc module, then follow the instructions
given in the tutorial.
